The research gap is clear now: public posts on tutorial writing stay at “know your audience” and “be clear,” while the stronger sources treat tutorials as pedagogy with reliability constraints. I’m drafting around that distinction and then I’ll run a constraint pass for sentence starts, banned patterns, and link quality before I save the file.
