/Users/ninad/Development/NinadPathak/output/blog/state-of-open-source-memory-2026/index.html:120:      "item": "https://ninadpathak.com/blog/state-of-open-source-memory-2026/"
/Users/ninad/Development/NinadPathak/output/blog/state-of-open-source-memory-2026/index.html:137:      <li><a href="/blog/"      class="nav-link active">Writing</a></li>
/Users/ninad/Development/NinadPathak/output/blog/state-of-open-source-memory-2026/index.html:166:    <a href="/blog/"      class="mobile-nav-link">Writing</a>
/Users/ninad/Development/NinadPathak/output/blog/state-of-open-source-memory-2026/index.html:184:      <li class="breadcrumb-item"><a href="/blog/">Blog</a></li>
/Users/ninad/Development/NinadPathak/output/blog/state-of-open-source-memory-2026/index.html:194:      <a href="/blog/" class="back-link">← All posts</a>
/Users/ninad/Development/NinadPathak/output/blog/state-of-open-source-memory-2026/index.html:249:<p>This architecture solves the transparency problem. You can watch the agent manage its own state through tool calls. Such auditability is a hard requirement for the <a href="/blog/agent-harnesses/">dedicated agent harnesses</a> that power modern enterprise AI.</p>
/Users/ninad/Development/NinadPathak/output/blog/state-of-open-source-memory-2026/index.html:268:<p>MCP allows you to communicate with any memory server through a unified schema. It standardizes how you read resources and how you invoke tools across the network. This <a href="/blog/model-context-protocol-explained/">standardization of tool access</a> lets you swap memory backends without rewriting core logic.</p>
/Users/ninad/Development/NinadPathak/output/blog/state-of-open-source-memory-2026/index.html:280:<p>External state paired with <a href="/blog/prompt-caching-what-it-is-and-when-the-math-works/">prompt caching</a> reduces average input tokens by over 65%. This efficiency enables more frequent and deeper user interactions. It also drives user retention because your system feels uniquely personalized.</p>
/Users/ninad/Development/NinadPathak/output/blog/state-of-open-source-memory-2026/index.html:281:<p>Retrieving specific anchors from a local store is faster than processing a million-token window. <a href="/blog/time-to-first-token-ttft/">Time to First Token (TTFT)</a> is the most visible differentiator in the 2026 AI market. Lower latency directly improves the user experience.</p>
